---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Chips — Agent actions"
  description="Signed deep-link actions an AI assistant can mint on behalf of a user."
>
  <main style="max-width: 36rem; margin: 6rem auto; padding: 0 1.25rem;">
    <h1>Agent actions</h1>
    <p>
      AI assistants (ChatGPT, Claude) can fetch a URL on this site to obtain a
      signed deep link for a specific action. The link is short-lived and HMAC-signed;
      when the user clicks it, the site verifies the signature and runs the action
      behind a confirm step.
    </p>

    <h2>Available actions</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <code>greet</code> — say hello.<br />
        Mint endpoint: <code>GET https://connectchips.xyz/agent/greet?name=&lt;name&gt;</code>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to use this from a chat</h2>
    <p>
      Ask the assistant to fetch the mint URL with the parameters you want, then surface
      the signed link in its reply. Example prompt:
    </p>
    <pre><code>Fetch https://connectchips.xyz/agent/greet?name=Azim and give me the signed link from the response.</code></pre>
    <p>
      The response body contains a plain-text URL of the form
      <code>https://connectchips.xyz/act?t=&lt;token&gt;</code>. Click it to confirm and run.
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>
